I '''Lyman Reed Blake''' (Agostu 24, 1835 â€“ Octubri 3, 1883) metung yang [[United States|American]]ung  [[menimbentu]] a peparalanan ne ing metung a  [[makinang panayi]] para tayan nala deng lalam ning [[sapatus]] keng babo ning sapatus.<ref name="About">{{cite web
 | title = Lyman Reed Blake (1835 - 1883)
  | publisher = [[About.com]]
  | author = Mary Bellis
  | date = 
  | url = http://inventors.about.com/library/inventors/blblake.htm
  | accessdate = 2007-02-10 }}</ref> Mibait king South Abington, [[Massachusetts]], Blake megumpisa yang mangawang sapatus bilang kayang kalakal inyang mura ya pa idad, mumuna megobra ya keng kayang kapatad a lalaki i Samuel. Kaibat i Blake megobra ya keng [[menimbentu]] i  [[Isaac Singer]] a cumpania, [[Singer Corporation]], sasalansan no reng makinang panayi kareng fabrica da reng sapatus. Inyang 1856, meging neng kasosiu keng cumpaniang mangawang sapatus at gigisanan ne ing kayang oras keng pamnimbentung makina paa apabilis na ing [[pamangawang sapatus]].<ref>{{cite web
 | title = Lyman Reed Blake (1835 - 1883)
  | publisher = [[Encyclopedia Britannica]]
  | author = 
  | date = 
  | url = http://secure.britannica.com/eb/article-9001797/Lyman-Reed-Blake#292429.hook
  | accessdate = 2007-02-10 }}</ref> 

Kaibat ning aduang banus, inyang Juliu 6, 1858, i Blake mektanggap yang patent ibat keng gubiernu ning United States para keng kayang [[makinang panayi]] para asopan neng ipakat ing lalam ning sapatus keng babo.<ref>{{cite web
 | title = July 6, 1858 in History
  | publisher = Brainymedia.com
  | author = 
  | date = 
  | url = http://www.brainyhistory.com/events/1858/july_6_1858_53821.html
  | accessdate = 2007-02-10 }}</ref> The sewing machine helped permit the production of low-cost shoes by eliminating the heavy work of hand sewing. Blake then sold the patent to Gordon McKay a year after for $8,000 in cash and a $62,000 share of future profits.<ref>{{cite web
 | title = Lasting Impressions
  | publisher = [[Harvard Magazine]]
  | author = Edward Tenner
  | date = 2000
  | url = http://people.deas.harvard.edu/~jones/mckay/article.html
  | accessdate = 2007-02-15 }}</ref> Blake later worked for McKay from 1861 until his retirement in 1874, working on improving the machine.<ref name="About"/> The McKay sole-sewing machine was at the top of the market for twenty-one years in both the [[United States]] and [[Great Britain]]. Blake died on October 5, 1883 at the age of 48.<ref>{{cite web
 | title = Today in Science History
